Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp with Helios head symbol. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 200, 5 or 173, 15. Name Euphranor. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0360.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1035)
